node.text: High winds smearing the skies into endless #lenticular clouds high over #Boulder, CO
Boulder Colorado ❤️ - Good to be home

There are few places as magical as the poles and the residents that inhabit them - A #polarBear cub spinning around to give me one last look before dashing to catch up to mom. These fleeting encounters are some of my very favorite, frozen moments in time taken in a part of the world changing more rapidly than anywhere else on the planet. @sealegacy
Merry Christmas everyone!
One from the archives of #gardenOfTheGods - happy #ChriatmasEve !! / photographed on Fuji #velvia on @nikonusa F5

Summer in southern #greenland is explosively vibrant with wildflowers, endless mountain ranges and aqua blue fjords. @mikelibecki setting up camp on the fly during a summit push with @ethan_pringle & @angelajpayne
If you’re gonna eat off of an alligators back, you better be quick on the exit! Photographed for @nikonusa 💥

Fiery sunset lighting up the skies over the icy waters of the #LemaireChannel on the #Antarctica Peninsula. The icy poles of the planet are changing more rapidly than anywhere else in the world and it’s never been more important to care about pollution and carbon legislation. Photographed on assignment along side friends @paulnicklen @mitty @andy_mann @ianvaso / for @natgeo @sealegacy

The beauty and mystery of Colombia’s Santa Marta mountains is a thing that gets in your soul and stays with you 🇨🇴 / Great memories with this crew - @wherenextlife @greggbleakney @julianmanrique @federicopardophoto @_josecastano @diegocolombiabirding
Patagonia sunrise illuminating the landscape over Torres Del Paine - This print and more are currently available at @natgeofineart galleries
This cow in #Kunming, China looking pretty unimpressed with @cedarwright’s summit push up this mini karst. Photographed on assignment for @natgeo on a really fun trip through southern China 🇨🇳

I feel ya #walrus, being a new dad has me feelin kinda like this these days. My wife @danahrichardson and I are slowly adjusting to the new sleep schedule and are in full team mode at the moment, wouldn’t trade it for anything but some extra 💤 would be nice 🙃

Everyone likes a good memory and it’s been funny watching my dog Vesper stare at the Google Nest screen as it rotates through photos from some of my favorite wild life shoots, expeditions and just casual outings from over the years. @GoogleNest recently sent me one of these and it’s been the perfect addition to the house, thanks google! #giftFromGoogle
Savage beauty high over Oklahoma 🌩 ❤️ / #stormchasing with @skiparmstrong @krystlejwright @nampix @tobypike

Of all animals I’ve ever watched spar, these young #giraffes were without a doubt the gentlest I’ve ever seen. When large bulls go at it it’s thunderous, however these two young ones here were playfully learning and not trying to injure one another. This behavior is known as #necking - @jabulanisafari / filmed handheld on the @nikonusa #Z6 with a 600mm f/4

Dark skies over #illouetteFalls in @yosemitenps - I shot this photo in 2005 after torrential rain flooded the valley floor, barring all exits due to submerged, and in some cases destroyed roads. I had woken up soaking wet with 4 inches of water inside my tent, a scene that was as cool as it sounds. I grabbed my camera bag and all of my wet belongings and ran to the truck to meet my friend @max_and_his_human where we laughed it off and cranked the heat, weathering the storm for the next 24 hours. I shot this photo sometime later when we were finally permitted to leave the park. This frame here was taken on a Pentax 6X7 on Fuji film.
A clutch of #Rhea chicks moving low and fast through a meadow in Patagonia. These little birds have to be fast, alert and on constant lookout for predators like Andean fox, wild cats and pumas.
Leading lines pushing through #tolarGrande Argentina

I’m still adjusting to the sleepless nights of being a new dad and kinda feeling like this today. I’m very excited and loving it of course, but I’m learning to appreciate naps 😉 Photo here - A #caracara displaying some territorial behavior in Southern Chile
I ❤️ #Greenland 🇬🇱

Natives of the #Wayuu tribe of northern Colombia performing a ceremonial #CardinalDance in their village in Camarones, La Guajira. Traditional Wayuu music and dance is derived through their cultural history and rooted in their environment, often performed in gatherings during celebration and meetings. This dance here is the courtship of a man and a women, inspired by the resident bright red Cardinal often seen here in the arid Guajira Peninsula of northern Colombia. Swipe to see the dance and video what the beautiful #Cardinal looks like. This sequence was shot during the filming of #TheBirders, a journey through Colombia exploring its wide diversity of birds, culture and music / @wherenextlife @greggbleakney @diegocolombiabirding @_josecastano @julianmanrique @federicopardophoto @sandraeichmannperret

One of those too-good-to-be-true moments over #Grindlewald Switzerland, this place seems to have a lot of them! This picturesque moment and scene was completely point shoot, taken right off of the balcony of the hotel with coffee in hand while teaching photography to students on an @natgeoexpeditions🇨🇭
Hard to beat the desert in the winter ❄️ Archive shot of my friend @joekinder looking strong on a first ascent he established high over Hurricane UT

There’s just some locations and scenes that are completely surreal. I’ve photographed this little Cyprus tree on a handful of occasion, it’s a classic nesting sight for ospreys and an absolute point-and-shoot composition, a total gift. Photographed for @nikonusa

Barnacle covered pillars at low tide along the Pismo California Pier at sunset. It’s pretty hard to have a bad day on the California coastline. I stumbled upon this scene while photographing California’s Highway 1 for a @nikonusa campaign for the D500 release back in 2015.
